{"title_page": "Qaghans of the Turkic khaganates", "text_new": "'''Kahagan''' (Qaghan) was a title used by the [[Turkic people]] of the Medieval Ages. The [[Turkic Khaganate]] (aka [[G\u00f6kt\u00fcrks]]) was a vast empire in Central Asia and Mongolia between 552 and 745. It was a confederation of Turkic tribes. Their history is turbulent. In the 6th century, they challenged the power of China. At the end of the century following a [[G\u00f6kt\u00fcrk civil war|civil war]], the khaganate was divided into eastern and western wings. In the second half of the 7th century, both wings were defeated by the [[Tang China]]. However, in 682 they regained their independence.\n\n==Qaghans of the Turkic Khaganate==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\"\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=\"#FFFF00\"|Title\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=green|Personal name and other title.\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=pink|Qatun\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=\"#FF0000\"|Throne\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=blue|Note\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Bumin Qaghan]] / Illig Qaghan (Yii)<br />\u4f0a\u5229\u53ef\u6c57\n|\"Tumen\"<br />\"\u571f\u9580\" / \"\u571f\u95e8\"\n|[[Princess Changle]]<br />\u9577\u6a02\u516c\u4e3b / \u957f\u4e50\u516c\u4e3b<br />From [[Western Wei]]\n|552\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Issik Qaghan]]<br />\u4e59\u606f\u8a18\u53ef\u6c57 / \u4e59\u606f\u8bb0\u53ef\u6c57\n|Keluo / K'o-lo<br />\u79d1\u7f85 / \u79d1\u7f57\n|\n|552\u2013553\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Muqan Qaghan]]<br />\u6728\u687f\u53ef\u6c57 / \u6728\u6746\u53ef\u6c57\n|Yandou / Yen-to<br />\u71d5\u90fd, \"\u4fdf\u65a4\"\n|\n|553\u2013572\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Taspar Qaghan]] (Tuobo)<br />\u4f57\u7f3d\u53ef\u6c57 / \u4f57\u94b5\u53ef\u6c57\n|\n|\n|572\u2013581\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan<ref Name=\"Deny\">{{cite book\n |author=Jean Deny |author2=Louis Bazin |author3=Hans Robert Roemer |author4=Gy\u00f6rgy Hazai |author5=Wolfgang-Ekkehard Scharlipp\n  | title =History of the Turkic Peoples in the Pre-Islamic Period\n  | publish