n]]<br />\u62d3\u897f\u53ef\u6c57\n|<br />\u5310\u4ff1\n|\n|716\u2013717\n|Son of Qapaghan Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Bilge Qaghan]]<br />\u6bd7\u4f3d\u53ef\u6c57\n|B\u00f6g\u00fc<br />\u9ed8\u68d8\u9023 / \u9ed8\u68d8\u8fde\n|[[Po Beg]]\n|717\u2013734\n|Son of Ilterish Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Yiran Qaghan]]<br />\u4f0a\u7136\u53ef\u6c57\n| -\n|\n|734-739\n|Son of Bilge Khagan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Tengri Qaghan]]<br />\u767b\u5229\u53ef\u6c57\n| -\n|\n|739\u2013741\n|Son of Bilge Khagan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Kutluk Yabgu Khagan|Kutluk Yabgu Qhagan]]\n|<br />\u9aa8\u5484\n|\n|741\u2013742\n| \n|-align=\"center\"\n| [[Ashina Shi]]<br />\u9821\u8dcc\u4f0a\u65bd\u53ef\u6c57 / \u9889\u8dcc\u4f0a\u65bd\u53ef\u6c57\n|\n|\n|742\u2013744\n| Uti Beg\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[\u00d6zmi\u015f Khagan]]<br />\u70cf\u8607\u7c73\u65bd\u53ef\u6c57 / \u4e4c\u82cf\u7c73\u65bd\u53ef\u6c57\n|\n|\n|742\u2013744\n|Son of Pan Kul Tigin\n|-align=\"center\"\n|White Eyebrow Qaghan <br />\u767d\u7709\u53ef\u6c57\n|Kulun beg <br /> \u9dbb\u96b4\u5310 / \u9e58\u9647\u5310\n|\n|744-745\n|Son of Pan Kul Tigin\n|-align=\"center\"\n|Eltemish Kagan<ref name=\"Yu. Zuev, p. 233\">Yu. Zuev (I\ufe20U\ufe21. A. Zuev) (2002) {{in lang|ru}}, ''Early T\u00fcrks: Essays on history and ideology'' ([https://openlibrary.org/b/OL13632412M/Rannie-ti%EF%B8%A0u%EF%B8%A1rki Rannie ti\ufe20u\ufe21rki: ocherki istorii i ideologii]), [[Almaty]], Daik-Press, p.&nbsp;233, {{Listed Invalid ISBN|9985-4-4152-9}}.</ref>\n|\n|\n|747\u2013759\n|Son of Bilge Khagan<ref>[http://bitig.org/?lang=e&mod=1&tid=1&oid=14&m=1]</ref>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|B\u00fcg\u00fc Qaghan<ref name=\"Yu. Zuev, p. 233\"/>\n|\n|\n|759\u2013779\n|\n|}\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{G\u00f6kt\u00fcrks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gokturk Kagans}}\n[[Category:G\u00f6kt\u00fcrks|Qagans]]\n[[Category:Lists of monarchs]]\n[[Category:Turkic dynasties]]\n", "text_old": "'''Kahagan''' (Qaghan) was a title used by the [[Turkic people]] of the Medieval Ages. The [[Turkic Khaganate]] (aka [[G\u00f6kt\u00fcrks]]) was a vast empire in Central Asia and Mongolia between 552 and 745. It was a confederation of Turkic tribes. Their history is turbulent. In the 6th century, they challenged the power of China. At the end of the century following a [[G\u00f6kt\u00fcrk civil war|civil war]], the khaganate was divided into eastern and western wings. In the second half of the 7th century, both wings were defeated by the [[Tang China]]. However, in 682 they regained their independence.\n\n==Qaghans of the Turkic Khaganate==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\"\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=\"#FFFF00\"|Title\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=green|Personal name and other title.\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=pink|Qatun\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=\"#FF0000\"|Throne\n!width=\"225\" bgcolor=blue|Note\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Bumin Qaghan]] / Illig Qaghan (Yii)<br />\u4f0a\u5229\u53ef\u6c57\n|\"Tumen\"<br />\"\u571f\u9580\" / \"\u571f\u95e8\"\n|[[Princess Changle]]<br />\u9577\u6a02\u516c\u4e3b / \u957f\u4e50\u516c\u4e3b<br />From [[Western Wei]]\n|552\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Issik Qaghan]]<br />\u4e59\u606f\u8a18\u53ef\u6c57 / \u4e59\u606f\u8bb0\u53ef\u6c57\n|Keluo / K'o-lo<br />\u79d1\u7f85 / \u79d1\u7f57\n|\n|552\u2013553\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Muqan Qaghan]]<br />\u6728\u687f\u53ef\u6c57 / \u6728\u6746\u53ef\u6c57\n|Yandou / Yen-to<br />\u71d5\u90fd, \"\u4fdf\u65a4\"\n|\n|553\u2013572\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[Taspar Qaghan]] (Tuobo)<br />\u4f57\u7f3d\u53ef\u6c57 / \u4f57\u94b5\u53ef\u6c57\n|\n|\n|572\u2013581\n|Son of Bumin Qaghan<ref Name=\"Deny\">{{cite book\n |author=Jean Deny |author2=Louis Bazin |author3=Hans Robert Roemer |author4=Gy\u00f6rgy Hazai |author5=Wolfgang-Ekkehard Scharlipp\n  | title =History of the Turkic Peoples in the Pre-Islamic Period\n  | publisher =Schwarz\n  | year =2000\n  | location =\n  | pages =108\n  | url =https://books.google.com/?id=86g2AAAAIAAJ&q=Taspar+Khan&dq=Taspar+Khan\n  | doi 